caption: Table 1: Comparison of MarketFCNet with baselines: n = 1,048,576 buyers and m = 10 goods. The GPU time for MarketFCNet represents the training time and testing time, respectively.
description: This table compares the performance of MarketFCNet against three baseline methods (Naive, EG, and EG-m) in approximating market equilibrium.  The metrics used for comparison include Nash Gap (NG), Violation of Allocation (VoA), Violation of Price (VoP), and GPU time.  The experiment used a market with 1,048,576 buyers and 10 goods.  The GPU time for MarketFCNet reflects both training and testing time.
